## Overview
This repository contains Quantum ESPRESSO (QE) input files for a set of benchmark systems used in Many-Body Perturbation Theory (MBPT) calculations.

The test systems are selected to systematically cover:
- Dimensionality: 0D, 1D, 2D, and 3D
- Electronic properties: metal, semiconductor, and insulator

By combining these categories, we construct a total of **12 classes** of test systems.  
Each class includes **two representative systems**, and all computational parameters have been carefully **converged**.

## Directory Structure

The directory structure follows a hierarchical naming convention:

``` #bash
├── doubt_system: contains some problematic systems.
├── <property>_<dimension>/
│   ├── <system> 
│       ├── QE 
│            ├── scf.in
│            ├── wfn.in
│            └── bgw.in

```

### Naming Rules
- `<property>`:  
  - `metal` (metallic systems)  
  - `semi` (semiconductors)  
  - `insulator` (insulating systems)

- `<dimension>`:  
  - `0D`, `1D`, `2D`, `3D`

- `<system_name>`: specific material or structure name

- `QE/`: contains Quantum ESPRESSO input files

## Example

An example system can be found in the `sample` directory:

├── semi_3D/
│   ├── GaN/
│       ├── QE/
│            ├── scf.in
│            ├── wfn.in
│            └── bgw.in
│       └── <Other_output_folders>

This provides a reference for file organization and input format.

## Notes

- All systems are prepared with convergence-tested parameters to ensure reliability in MBPT workflows.
- The dataset is intended for benchmarking, testing, and validation purposes.

## Requirements

- [Quantum ESPRESSO](https://www.quantum-espresso.org/)
- Should be compatible with QE 6.7 and later versions, with hdf5 supported.

